    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8e427351_9965f802",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/emulation/AndroidAsyncMessagePipe_unittest.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 130,
      "author": {
        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-22T21:06:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is often called with a particular timeout and the sleep is always 50 ms. Could there be a faster or more guaranteed way to make sure the event is processed?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 123,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 130,
        "endChar": 0
      },
      "revId": "115cb9677c2812287655c36de404de0fc2763c30",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "02571845_76c60cbd",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/emulation/AndroidAsyncMessagePipe_unittest.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 130,
      "author": {
        "id": 1233742
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-22T22:50:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hmm, possibly.  This is for the multithreaded test case, which intentionally does a sleep() to simulate a long-running process that replies later.  Until the sleep is done, looper::runOneIterationWithDeadlineMs returns instantly since it has no timers registered that it\u0027s waiting on, but I need to keep ticking until one gets registered.\n\nI could potentially introduce a new event that gets set after the worker thread\u0027s sendMessage() is complete, and then only call into the looper after that, but that may limit the scope of the test.  If you feel strongly about it and I can give that a go.",
      "parentUuid": "8e427351_9965f802",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 123,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 130,
        "endChar": 0
      },
      "revId": "115cb9677c2812287655c36de404de0fc2763c30",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e56a70eb_5d988b4d",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/emulation/AndroidAsyncMessagePipe_unittest.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 130,
      "author": {
        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-22T22:56:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Got it; it seems it would be vulnerable to flakes since the other thread could get scheduled away for much longer than its sleep value, especially in the build server environment. What if we spin forever on the looper, once every 50 ms, until a reply comes back?",
      "parentUuid": "02571845_76c60cbd",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 123,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 130,
        "endChar": 0
      },
      "revId": "115cb9677c2812287655c36de404de0fc2763c30",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "95853145_264acbd5",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/emulation/AndroidAsyncMessagePipe_unittest.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 130,
      "author": {
        "id": 1233742
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-23T00:56:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I could do that, but I was mostly concerned about having the test hang forever.  Maybe a much longer timeout?  10 seconds? 30 seconds?",
      "parentUuid": "e56a70eb_5d988b4d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 123,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 130,
        "endChar": 0
      },
      "revId": "115cb9677c2812287655c36de404de0fc2763c30",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "bae59968_3360ee14",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/emulation/AndroidAsyncMessagePipe_unittest.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 130,
      "author": {
        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-23T01:03:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ok, 10 or 30 seconds sounds pretty good (We have a code coverage build that seems to run slower than the other builds that go on).",
      "parentUuid": "95853145_264acbd5",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 123,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 130,
        "endChar": 0
      },
      "revId": "115cb9677c2812287655c36de404de0fc2763c30",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c4291d79_10c25ea2",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/emulation/AndroidAsyncMessagePipe_unittest.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 130,
      "author": {
        "id": 1233742
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-23T06:21:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Okay, this latest iteration should be an improvement.  I discovered I misread how runOneIterationWithDeadlineMs behaves, it always waits until the deadline before returning, and doesn\u0027t pick up new events until the very end, so this was always hitting the timeout duration.\n\nI changed this to take a TestEvent as a parameter, and repeatedly check if the event has been signaled while pumping in 50ms increments, with an overall timeout of 15 seconds.",
      "parentUuid": "bae59968_3360ee14",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 123,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 130,
        "endChar": 0
      },
      "revId": "115cb9677c2812287655c36de404de0fc2763c30",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
